_LOG

_runningMonitor

private final Object _runningMonitor
A mutex that protects _running.

_running

private boolean _running
_running is set to false in destroyInstance(). _running is examined by run() after each NormEvent.

Since Thread.stop() is deprecated, we use _running and _runningMonitor to tell run when to exit.

_normThread

private final Thread _normThread
The RunnableNormInstance needs its own Thread.

run

public void run()
run is an event loop. It keeps track of the available writing slots in the NormSession. It reports new Objects as they arrive from the sender. run loops continuously until _running is false.
